# URL triggers

There are a number of 'special' URL segments in Prontotype URLs that will trigger some specific behaviour - for instance pre-processing and serving up an [asset file]({{ pt.pages.getById('assets').getUrl() }}), triggering a [short URL redirect]({{ pt.pages.getById('pages-shorturls').getUrl() }}), and so on.

All of these trigger segments have default values which can be overridden in your config files should you wish  . To **disable** any of the special functionality triggered by these URLs, you can set the value of that trigger in your config file to `null`.

Below is the default set of trigger values:

<pre class="brush: yaml">triggers:
  data: _data
  shorturl: _p
  tools: _tools
  auth: _auth
  assets: _assets
  user: _user</pre>
  
To read more about the functionality each of these triggers expose, see the relevant docs page:

* `data`: [{{ pt.pages.getById('data').getTitle() }}]({{ pt.pages.getById('data').getUrl() }})
* `shorturl`: [{{ pt.pages.getById('pages-shorturls').getTitle() }}]({{ pt.pages.getById('pages-shorturls').getUrl() }})
